		<a class="post-link" href="https://freekorea.us/2019/12/16/review-sandra-fahy-dying-for-rights-columbia-university-press-2019/">

			<div class="post-thumbnail"><figure>
				<img width="345" height="250" src="https://freekorea.us/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Screen-Shot-2019-12-15-at-4.47.19-PM-345x250.png" class="attachment-cd-medium size-cd-medium wp-post-image" alt="" />			</figure></div>

			<div class="post-content">
									<div class="post-date">December 16, 2019</div>
				
				<h2 class="post-title">Review: Sandra Fahy, &#8220;Dying for Rights,&#8221; Columbia University Press, 2019</h2>

									<div class="post-excerpt"><p>&acirc;&euro;&oelig;In a penicillin bottle I wrote her date of birth, the day she died, and her name. I hung the bottle around her neck. I tied her hair. [The other prisoners and I] tied her legs. Her arms. We wrapped her body in a plastic bag. This is what happens in a prison camp in North Korea. That&acirc;&euro;&trade;s how we wrapped the dead bodies. When the warehouse has twenty dead bodies, we take those bodies to a place called the&#46;&#46;&#46;</p>
</div>
							</div>

		</a>

		<div class="post-meta">
							<span class="post-category">
					<span class="far fa-folder" aria-hidden="true"></span>
					<span class="screen-reader-text">Categories</span>
					<a href="https://freekorea.us/category/book-reviews/" rel="category tag">Books &amp; Films</a>				</span>
			
					</div>

	</div><!--/.post-inner-->
</article>
							
							
						
															
